Lists starts with 0
if negative, starting from end
can contain different data types

len()
- used to determine length

ACCESS LIST ITEMS
- use index number

ex: 
thislist = ["apple", "banana", "cherry"]
print(thislist[2]) #this will print cherry

thislist = ["apple", "banana", "cherry"]
print(thislist[-1]) #this will print cherry since it is negative mags-start sa end

IN RANGE USE ([index:index])
- the last number is EXCLUDED in range
- if walang start na nilagay, it will print from the very start.
- if walang end na nilagay, it will print until the end of list

ex:
thislist = ["apple", "banana", "cherry", "orange", "kiwi", "melon", "mango"]
print(thislist[-4:-1]) #this will print orange, kiwi, melon

thislist = ["apple", "banana", "cherry", "orange", "kiwi", "melon", "mango"]
print(thislist[:4]) #this will print apple, banana, cherry, orange

CHECKING IF LIST IS INCLUDED
- use in
thislist = ["apple", "banana", "cherry"]
if "apple" in thislist:
  print("Yes, 'apple' is in the fruits list")

CHANGE ITEM
thislist = ["apple", "banana", "cherry"]
thislist[1] = "blackcurrant"

print(thislist)

thislist = ["apple", "banana", "cherry"]
thislist[1:2] = ["blackcurrant", "watermelon"]

print(thislist)

LIST METHODS
- use append()


menu
[1] insert items
